1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:10,000
[English subtitles are available]

2
00:01:40,500 --> 00:01:45,729
[Follow Your Heart]

3
00:02:18,550 --> 00:02:21,020
[Episode 2]

4
00:02:31,550 --> 00:02:32,310
It's him!

5
00:02:33,030 --> 00:02:34,110
Oh no.

6
00:02:34,630 --> 00:02:36,710
Why is he staring at me?

7
00:02:37,310 --> 00:02:39,190
His clothes and hairstyle...

8
00:02:44,140 --> 00:02:45,060
You are?

9
00:02:52,079 --> 00:02:53,500
Why did he touch me?

10
00:02:53,950 --> 00:02:54,950
What does he want?

11
00:02:59,390 --> 00:03:00,079
This...

12
00:03:00,620 --> 00:03:01,320
lady.

13
00:03:02,310 --> 00:03:03,230
It's late.

14
00:03:03,510 --> 00:03:05,240
What are you doing in the water?

15
00:03:07,579 --> 00:03:08,110
You...

16
00:03:09,560 --> 00:03:10,400
Miss?

17
00:03:10,550 --> 00:03:11,880
He's kidding me, right?

18
00:03:13,870 --> 00:03:14,950
But I don't think

19
00:03:14,950 --> 00:03:16,480
he's joking with me either.

20
00:03:17,270 --> 00:03:19,030
Or is it because it's dark now,

21
00:03:19,870 --> 00:03:21,400
and he can't see me clearly?

22
00:03:28,070 --> 00:03:29,329
Do I have to pull you up?

23
00:03:29,960 --> 00:03:31,610
No, I'll be exposed.

24
00:03:34,550 --> 00:03:35,630
Search every ship!

25
00:03:35,710 --> 00:03:36,270
Yes.

26
00:03:50,030 --> 00:03:51,490
Hurry! Search carefully.

27
00:03:59,220 --> 00:04:00,620
Some of you go over there!

28
00:04:20,870 --> 00:04:21,470
Miss.

29
00:04:22,390 --> 00:04:23,120
Are you okay?

30
00:04:26,860 --> 00:04:27,950
You guys go over there.

31
00:04:27,950 --> 00:04:28,440
Yes.

32
00:04:30,070 --> 00:04:30,550
Get up.

33
00:04:30,550 --> 00:04:32,010
Hurry! Search carefully.

34
00:04:32,550 --> 00:04:33,550
Come on, get up.

35
00:04:34,270 --> 00:04:34,800
This way.

36
00:04:35,510 --> 00:04:36,460
Search carefully.

37
00:04:36,460 --> 00:04:37,120
Over there.

38
00:04:39,710 --> 00:04:40,800
Be careful!

39
00:04:53,470 --> 00:04:53,950
Hey!

40
00:05:06,790 --> 00:05:07,380
Miss.

41
00:05:09,150 --> 00:05:10,280
Are you really okay?

42
00:05:14,470 --> 00:05:14,930
Well...

43
00:05:16,030 --> 00:05:16,830
Your hands,

44
00:05:19,420 --> 00:05:20,530
and your feet...

45
00:05:38,390 --> 00:05:39,310
Stop trying to hide.

46
00:05:39,310 --> 00:05:40,440
The boat is rocking.

47
00:05:42,620 --> 00:05:43,150
Stop.

48
00:05:45,070 --> 00:05:46,600
It's a man's hands and feet.

49
00:05:47,190 --> 00:05:48,850
Why did he disguise as a woman?

50
00:06:13,830 --> 00:06:15,060
It's you again.

51
00:06:15,510 --> 00:06:16,550
By the sound of his voice,

52
00:06:16,550 --> 00:06:17,780
it's Lieutenant General Li,

53
00:06:17,780 --> 00:06:20,580
who almost took me away from the theatre last time.

54
00:06:21,790 --> 00:06:22,550
Officer.

55
00:06:22,870 --> 00:06:23,990
How have you been?

56
00:06:24,390 --> 00:06:25,230
Who's inside?

57
00:06:27,550 --> 00:06:28,870
It's a lady in there.

58
00:06:29,310 --> 00:06:30,310
Please excuse us.

59
00:06:30,430 --> 00:06:31,150
A lady?

60
00:06:32,840 --> 00:06:34,040
You mean a courtesan?

61
00:06:34,680 --> 00:06:35,760
Have you seen a man?

62
00:06:36,680 --> 00:06:37,470
They are looking for

63
00:06:37,470 --> 00:06:38,190
the man who just came up

64
00:06:38,190 --> 00:06:39,470
dressed as a woman?

65
00:06:40,040 --> 00:06:41,210
Did this man have something to do with

66
00:06:41,210 --> 00:06:43,070
the riot at the General's Residence?

67
00:06:43,070 --> 00:06:44,400
He must know something.

68
00:06:44,830 --> 00:06:45,510
A man?

69
00:06:47,600 --> 00:06:48,530
What kind of man?

70
00:06:48,910 --> 00:06:50,310
What's his age or height?

71
00:06:50,550 --> 00:06:52,280
Any distinguishing features?

72
00:06:52,310 --> 00:06:54,300
A man! That's it!

73
00:06:56,390 --> 00:06:56,990
Officer.

74
00:06:57,530 --> 00:06:58,590
It's already late.

75
00:06:58,830 --> 00:07:00,750
Yet, you are disturbing everyone with your search.

76
00:07:00,750 --> 00:07:01,870
Besides his gender,

77
00:07:01,870 --> 00:07:03,160
you can't even tell me the characteristics

78
00:07:03,160 --> 00:07:04,180
of the person you are looking for.

79
00:07:04,180 --> 00:07:06,110
It's dark, and it happened all of a sudden.

80
00:07:06,110 --> 00:07:07,510
I didn't see him clearly!

81
00:07:08,830 --> 00:07:10,190
Who are you putting on airs with?

82
00:07:10,190 --> 00:07:11,470
You've misunderstood.

83
00:07:11,470 --> 00:07:12,470
I just want to say

84
00:07:13,190 --> 00:07:14,260
there is no man here

85
00:07:14,260 --> 00:07:15,590
that you're looking for.

86
00:07:15,590 --> 00:07:17,390
That's not up to you to conclude.

87
00:07:17,750 --> 00:07:19,390
We wouldn't know until we search.

88
00:07:19,390 --> 00:07:19,980
Officer.

89
00:07:22,830 --> 00:07:24,270
Without an official order,

90
00:07:24,270 --> 00:07:26,070
it's not right to trespass

91
00:07:26,480 --> 00:07:27,830
people's private property.

92
00:07:27,830 --> 00:07:29,830
So what? I'll just break in.

93
00:07:33,790 --> 00:07:34,470
Officer.

94
00:07:36,030 --> 00:07:37,630
The General's Residence will be

95
00:07:37,630 --> 00:07:38,110
held accountable

96
00:07:38,110 --> 00:07:39,840
for your stubborn insistence.

97
00:07:40,190 --> 00:07:41,920
Are you sure you want to do this?

98
00:07:43,180 --> 00:07:44,290
That makes sense.

99
00:07:44,950 --> 00:07:45,910
He's saving me?

100
00:07:46,520 --> 00:07:48,320
He doesn't even know who I am now.

101
00:07:48,460 --> 00:07:49,590
Why is he helping me?

102
00:07:49,750 --> 00:07:51,510
No, I can't get him into trouble.

103
00:07:51,510 --> 00:07:52,750
I will insist on

104
00:07:52,750 --> 00:07:54,030
searching today.

105
00:07:54,150 --> 00:07:54,650
Lieutenant General Li,

106
00:07:54,650 --> 00:07:55,580
he's over there!

107
00:07:55,910 --> 00:07:56,310
Go!

108
00:08:25,130 --> 00:08:28,980
[Notice of arrest]

109
00:08:27,180 --> 00:08:29,090
Isn't she the female doctor named Yan Nanxing?

110
00:08:29,090 --> 00:08:30,730
Didn't she run a free clinic just a few days ago?

111
00:08:30,730 --> 00:08:32,390
She looked like a good person.

112
00:08:33,120 --> 00:08:34,190
When she was treating

113
00:08:34,190 --> 00:08:35,100
Madam last night,

114
00:08:35,100 --> 00:08:36,630
a man suddenly appeared.

115
00:08:36,780 --> 00:08:38,470
General and Madam suspect that

116
00:08:38,470 --> 00:08:40,070
they colluded

117
00:08:40,070 --> 00:08:41,350
to murder Madam.

118
00:08:41,590 --> 00:08:42,590
And I heard that

119
00:08:42,590 --> 00:08:43,360
many strange things

120
00:08:43,360 --> 00:08:45,240
have been happening in the nearby villages.

121
00:08:45,240 --> 00:08:45,950
Maybe it's the work of

122
00:08:45,950 --> 00:08:47,810
this mother-and-daughter gang.

123
00:08:50,820 --> 00:08:52,320
If we go with what you said,

124
00:08:52,350 --> 00:08:53,510
there should be one more man from last night

125
00:08:53,510 --> 00:08:55,310
that the General's Residence is looking for.

126
00:08:55,310 --> 00:08:56,470
Why is it just the two of them

127
00:08:56,470 --> 00:08:57,910
on the wanted poster?

128
00:08:59,950 --> 00:09:02,550
That means the mother and daughter are the key.

129
00:09:02,710 --> 00:09:03,310
By the way,

130
00:09:04,150 --> 00:09:04,750
Phantom Physician

131
00:09:04,750 --> 00:09:06,750
is staying at a shabby temple 20 miles away from the city.

132
00:09:06,750 --> 00:09:08,750
She seems to be waiting for someone.

133
00:09:09,110 --> 00:09:11,110
She must be waiting for Yan Nanxing.

134
00:09:12,830 --> 00:09:14,240
We must find Yan Nanxing

135
00:09:14,240 --> 00:09:15,429
before Nan Jifeng does.

136
00:09:15,429 --> 00:09:16,670
I want to know

137
00:09:17,060 --> 00:09:17,960
what happened at

138
00:09:17,960 --> 00:09:19,960
Nan Jifeng's residence that night.

139
00:09:20,760 --> 00:09:21,750
It even drove Nan Jifeng

140
00:09:21,750 --> 00:09:23,950
to issue an arrest warrant far and wide.

141
00:09:24,220 --> 00:09:25,880
It must be something serious.

142
00:09:25,970 --> 00:09:28,500
You suspect it's related to the Zornia plant?

143
00:09:30,550 --> 00:09:31,150
Yao.

144
00:09:32,030 --> 00:09:33,190
I'm heading out of town.

145
00:09:33,190 --> 00:09:35,250
You stay in the town to look for clues.

146
00:09:36,590 --> 00:09:37,520
At the same time,

147
00:09:37,910 --> 00:09:39,170
get rid of our stalker.

148
00:09:40,510 --> 00:09:42,510
But Sir, you don't recognize faces,

149
00:09:42,550 --> 00:09:44,550
nor are you familiar with the place.

150
00:09:44,990 --> 00:09:46,590
This isn't my first mission.

151
00:09:46,830 --> 00:09:48,360
What are you worried about?

152
00:09:48,480 --> 00:09:49,410
For some reason,

153
00:09:49,910 --> 00:09:51,230
I feel that you've

154
00:09:51,510 --> 00:09:53,110
met your opponent this time.

155
00:09:53,910 --> 00:09:55,110
Just Yan Nanxing?

156
00:10:16,880 --> 00:10:17,990
It's been four or five days.

157
00:10:17,990 --> 00:10:19,670
Why haven't I changed back?

158
00:10:21,830 --> 00:10:23,010
Oh dear moon.

159
00:10:23,170 --> 00:10:25,370
You're really messing with me, aren't you?

160
00:10:25,370 --> 00:10:26,460
When you have a full moon,

161
00:10:26,460 --> 00:10:27,510
I'll get my period.

162
00:10:27,510 --> 00:10:29,070
And when I get my period, I will shapeshift into someone else.

163
00:10:29,070 --> 00:10:30,390
And I always get in trouble whenever I shapeshift.

164
00:10:30,390 --> 00:10:32,270
And whenever I am in trouble, I will rant to you.

165
00:10:32,270 --> 00:10:33,530
Aren't you tired of it?

166
00:10:33,750 --> 00:10:36,060
Even if you aren't, I am.

167
00:11:47,590 --> 00:11:48,720
That was a hard fall.

168
00:11:50,030 --> 00:11:51,010
It hurts so much.

169
00:11:59,840 --> 00:12:01,240
I've shapeshifted back!

170
00:12:04,860 --> 00:12:06,220
When did it happen?

171
00:12:14,430 --> 00:12:15,230
This weather

172
00:12:15,870 --> 00:12:17,200
is more fickle than I am.

173
00:12:20,160 --> 00:12:21,080
Forget it.

174
00:12:21,970 --> 00:12:23,370
I can't afford to offend.

175
00:12:33,190 --> 00:12:34,070
Did she become a snail

176
00:12:34,070 --> 00:12:35,190
or a turtle?

177
00:12:35,210 --> 00:12:36,810
Why hasn't she come back yet?

178
00:13:10,310 --> 00:13:12,310
Why did the whistle suddenly stop?

179
00:13:13,390 --> 00:13:15,320
The old lady is slacking off again.

180
00:13:16,070 --> 00:13:18,000
Fortunately, I'm already nearby.

181
00:13:21,930 --> 00:13:23,320
Where are you?

182
00:13:29,550 --> 00:13:31,270
Sir, I'm sorry.

183
00:13:34,790 --> 00:13:35,830
Madam.

184
00:13:38,850 --> 00:13:39,530
Aren't you being

185
00:13:39,530 --> 00:13:41,390
too accurate with the horse dung?

186
00:13:41,590 --> 00:13:42,870
Oh, you're a girl.

187
00:13:43,150 --> 00:13:44,310
I'm really sorry.

188
00:13:44,670 --> 00:13:46,190
If you don't mind,

189
00:13:46,480 --> 00:13:47,630
go in and get changed

190
00:13:47,650 --> 00:13:48,600
before you continue.

191
00:13:48,600 --> 00:13:49,230
Forget it.

192
00:13:49,950 --> 00:13:51,080
I have something on.

193
00:13:52,510 --> 00:13:53,430
See you.

194
00:14:10,030 --> 00:14:10,870
Let go of me.

195
00:14:14,790 --> 00:14:15,920
Handsome young man,

196
00:14:16,060 --> 00:14:17,590
why are you tying me up here?

197
00:14:20,460 --> 00:14:21,190
Don't worry.

198
00:14:21,670 --> 00:14:22,670
I won't roast you.

199
00:14:24,720 --> 00:14:26,200
Don't burn the house down.

200
00:14:26,550 --> 00:14:27,390
Let go of me.

201
00:14:27,870 --> 00:14:28,470
Tell me.

202
00:14:29,990 --> 00:14:31,750
What did you and your daughter

203
00:14:31,750 --> 00:14:32,590
do in Heman?

204
00:14:33,150 --> 00:14:35,350
Why does General Nan want you arrested?

205
00:14:36,350 --> 00:14:37,870
Why should I tell you?

206
00:14:39,100 --> 00:14:40,700
Tell me everything you know.

207
00:14:41,390 --> 00:14:42,270
If your daughter

208
00:14:42,270 --> 00:14:43,730
has been wrongly accused,

209
00:14:44,830 --> 00:14:46,360
I can guarantee her safety.

210
00:14:49,870 --> 00:14:51,070
Why are you laughing?

211
00:14:52,910 --> 00:14:54,390
You don't look like

212
00:14:55,070 --> 00:14:57,400
someone sent by the General's Residence.

213
00:14:57,750 --> 00:14:58,790
Are you here

214
00:14:58,830 --> 00:15:00,290
to deal with that General?

215
00:15:27,990 --> 00:15:28,920
What do you want?

216
00:15:33,030 --> 00:15:33,670
Be quiet.

217
00:15:59,380 --> 00:16:00,240
It's him again.

218
00:16:05,190 --> 00:16:06,520
The smell of horse dung?

219
00:16:10,670 --> 00:16:11,530
A horse dealer?

220
00:16:15,910 --> 00:16:16,830
Young man,

221
00:16:17,430 --> 00:16:18,270
please...

222
00:16:19,530 --> 00:16:21,130
find somewhere else to rest.

223
00:16:22,920 --> 00:16:24,320
He doesn't recognize me?

224
00:16:24,590 --> 00:16:26,310
Or did he forget me so soon?

225
00:16:27,200 --> 00:16:27,830
My face

226
00:16:27,850 --> 00:16:29,650
might not be the most beautiful,

227
00:16:29,990 --> 00:16:31,070
but at least

228
00:16:31,070 --> 00:16:32,270
I'm pretty as a fairy.

229
00:16:32,900 --> 00:16:33,910
How could he forget me

230
00:16:33,910 --> 00:16:34,870
so quickly?

231
00:16:46,030 --> 00:16:47,560
There's a teahouse nearby.

232
00:16:47,590 --> 00:16:49,070
Go have some tea.

233
00:16:49,280 --> 00:16:50,480
Consider it my treat.

234
00:17:03,560 --> 00:17:05,390
Is he trying to warn me of danger?

235
00:17:06,110 --> 00:17:08,510
Could it be an ambush by the authorities?

236
00:17:13,070 --> 00:17:13,590
Go.

237
00:17:32,070 --> 00:17:32,630
Thanks.

238
00:17:49,520 --> 00:17:51,079
The older, the wiser.

239
00:17:51,109 --> 00:17:52,550
I'm aging like fine wine.

240
00:17:52,910 --> 00:17:54,910
Handsome young man, get some sleep.

241
00:18:28,950 --> 00:18:30,580
I knew you were unreliable.

242
00:18:30,950 --> 00:18:31,990
What do you mean,

243
00:18:31,990 --> 00:18:33,720
"Everything's fine with Mum?"

244
00:18:34,110 --> 00:18:34,920
What now?

245
00:18:34,970 --> 00:18:36,300
You can't even find him.

246
00:18:38,110 --> 00:18:40,190
Let's get rid of your bad luck.

247
00:18:41,120 --> 00:18:43,270
Do you know how many constables were there?

248
00:18:43,270 --> 00:18:44,630
I've been dodging left and right,

249
00:18:44,630 --> 00:18:45,760
trying to avoid them

250
00:18:45,870 --> 00:18:47,150
like a wild monkey.

251
00:18:47,590 --> 00:18:49,110
I'm exhausted.

252
00:18:49,750 --> 00:18:50,350
Listen.

253
00:18:50,920 --> 00:18:52,370
We're in trouble this time.

254
00:18:52,370 --> 00:18:53,590
We're being blamed for all the bad things done by

255
00:18:53,590 --> 00:18:54,630
female thieves in the neighboring provinces

256
00:18:54,630 --> 00:18:56,160
who haven't been arrested.

257
00:18:56,310 --> 00:18:57,030
Really?

258
00:18:59,470 --> 00:19:00,400
Who can we blame?

259
00:19:00,630 --> 00:19:01,760
It's all your fault.

260
00:19:02,390 --> 00:19:04,170
You insisted on running away from home.

261
00:19:04,170 --> 00:19:05,230
If you didn't,

262
00:19:05,350 --> 00:19:06,230
how could you be poisoned by

263
00:19:06,230 --> 00:19:07,680
some unbelievable shapeshifting poison?

264
00:19:07,680 --> 00:19:08,830
If you weren't poisoned,

265
00:19:08,830 --> 00:19:09,470
we wouldn't need to

266
00:19:09,470 --> 00:19:10,370
go to the General's Residence

267
00:19:10,370 --> 00:19:12,030
to steal the damned antidote.

268
00:19:12,750 --> 00:19:14,230
How dare you blame me?

269
00:19:14,550 --> 00:19:15,460
If you hadn't used me

270
00:19:15,460 --> 00:19:16,790
as a guinea pig since young to test drugs,

271
00:19:16,790 --> 00:19:17,830
would I run away from home?

272
00:19:17,830 --> 00:19:18,550
If I hadn't,

273
00:19:18,630 --> 00:19:19,950
would I even get poisoned?

274
00:19:19,950 --> 00:19:20,950
If I hadn't,

275
00:19:20,950 --> 00:19:21,910
would I shapeshift every month

276
00:19:21,910 --> 00:19:22,910
when I'm on my period?

277
00:19:22,910 --> 00:19:24,190
It's all your fault.

278
00:19:25,310 --> 00:19:25,910
Forget it.

279
00:19:26,870 --> 00:19:28,530
I told you, we don't get along.

280
00:19:28,870 --> 00:19:29,550
As usual,

281
00:19:29,630 --> 00:19:30,490
let's split up.

282
00:19:35,550 --> 00:19:36,710
Fine, let's split.

283
00:19:37,590 --> 00:19:39,150
We're definitely not compatible in our ba-zi.

284
00:19:39,150 --> 00:19:41,180
We'll definitely be unlucky if we stay together.

285
00:19:41,180 --> 00:19:43,110
You've got the nerve to dislike me?

286
00:19:44,440 --> 00:19:45,030
So what?

287
00:19:45,630 --> 00:19:47,430
You're all grown up now.

288
00:19:47,470 --> 00:19:48,510
You can go to anywhere you want.

289
00:19:48,510 --> 00:19:49,610
What am I supposed to do with you?

290
00:19:49,610 --> 00:19:50,740
Then leave me alone.

291
00:20:01,020 --> 00:20:02,880
What? You're missing me already?

292
00:20:04,110 --> 00:20:05,110
